  <front>
    <title>PCP Server Selection</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-ietf-pcp-server-selection-01"/>
    <author initials="M." surname="Boucadair" fullname="Mohamed Boucadair"/>
    <author initials="R." surname="Penno" fullname="Reinaldo Penno"/>
    <author initials="D." surname="Wing" fullname="Dan Wing"/>
    <author initials="P." surname="Patil" fullname="Prashanth Patil"/>
    <author initials="T." surname="Reddy.K" fullname="Tirumaleswar Reddy.K"/>
    <date day="22" month="May" year="2013"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>This document specifies the behavior to be followed by the PCP client
   to contact its PCP server(s) when one or several PCP server names are
   configured.  Multiple names may be configured to a PCP client in some
   deployment contexts such as multi-homing.

   This document updates RFC6887.</t>
    </abstract>
